Short version — there are two paths:

## Minimum fix (1 file, fixes today's symptom)

`apps/web/src/features/onboarding/effects/useBackendSync.ts:175-187` — the `complete` handler writes the conversation id into the onboarding reducer but not into `useUserStore`. Mirror it:

```ts
complete: (p) => {
  dispatchRef.current({
    type: "serverPatch",
    patch: {
      first_message_conversation_id: p.conversation_id ?? undefined,
      phase: "personalization_complete",
    },
  });
  // mirror into the user store so ChatRenderer's isWelcomeConversation
  // flips true this session (without it, only a reload picks it up).
  if (p.conversation_id) {
    useUserStore.getState().updateUser({
      onboarding: {
        ...(useUserStore.getState().onboarding ?? { completed: true }),
        first_message_conversation_id: p.conversation_id,
      },
    });
  }
  closeWs();
},
```

Also patch `UserInfo.onboarding` in `apps/web/src/features/auth/api/authApi.ts:9-18` to include `first_message_conversation_id?: string` so the type matches the runtime shape.

After this, post-onboarding chat shows: `WelcomeChat` — the persona-tailored bubble ("Hey, welcome! I'm your GAIA…" → middle line tied to profession → "Just connect Calendar and Notion and I'll get to it!") + two buttons ("Connect your tools", "See what you can do"). The seeded holo wrap-up bubble stays in the conversation on disk but is suppressed by the existing `index === 0` rule in `ChatRenderer`.

## Clean fix (also rip out the dead weight)

On top of the above:

- `apps/api/app/utils/seeding_utils.py:261-270` — drop the `update_messages([...])` call so the seeded conversation is empty.
- `apps/web/src/features/chat/components/interface/ChatPage.tsx:216` — when `isWelcomeConversation`, route to `ChatWithMessages` even with zero messages (otherwise empty conversations fall into `NewChatLayout` and show the generic "How can I help?" starter, not `WelcomeChat`).
- `apps/web/src/features/chat/components/interface/ChatRenderer.tsx:241-251` — replace the `index === 0` swap with: if `isWelcomeConversation` and message list is empty, render `<WelcomeChat />`. No more suppression hack.

Same visible result, but nothing redundant left.

Which one do you want me to apply?

